The paper proposes a new approach for greybox fuzzing that addresses the problem of deeply nested conditional statements, which is a common issue in various software systems such as image and video decoders, network packet analyzers, and checksum tools. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach in finding new bugs and obtaining CVEs, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the implementation of the approach in a tool called Matryoshka, which implies that it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of strategies to find an input that satisfies all conditional statements simultaneously, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art fuzzers for comparison, which implies that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
